The paper deals with optimization problems in MIMO interference networks, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The paper also uses convex analysis, which is a common tool in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a novel iterative algorithm, which could be of interest to researchers in the systems and control (cs.SI) community.
